      <h3 class="my-3 text-center font-weight-bold">Issue</h3>
      <p>When I sketched my userflow I was hesitating if I should make "donate $1" as a button that
        changes the color/opacity when you click on it or a checkbox.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-6 px-5">
      <h3 class="my-3 text-center font-weight-bold">My actions</h3>
      <p>In order to figure out what works better I did some usability tests. The feedback I got shown
        that when users see the button, they expect it to send them to another page (which makes it unnecessary
         complicated). The checkbox indicates that the action can be made with 1 click.</p>
    </div>
