<div class="container w-60">
  <ul>
    <li>At our first wireframes, we tried to make the charity organization logo stand out, so we had it in a square.
       During some usability tests (I personally conducted 4 of them), we received feedback that it looks weird
       and doesn’t blend to Venmo's interface. So we <b>switched to the popular round shape.</b></li>
    <li>The common question from users was: "What if I want to donate more than a dollar?". We had lots of discussions
      at our team regarding this issue. We tried to switch to "Donate" instead, but then we got an insight that <b>users want
      to have an easy path</b> as well. We ended up with keeping both ways to please both our personas.</li>
  </ul>
</div>


